summary: Captain Marvel Graces The Cover of Empire Magazine
title: Captain Marvel Graces The Cover of Empire Magazine
body:
Marvel Studios new female-led 2019 superhero film, Captain Marvel, graces the cover of this month’s Empire Magazine.

The film is written and directed by Anna Boden and Ryan Fleck, with Geneva Robertson-Dworet and Jac Schaeffer also contributing to the screenplay. Brie Larson stars as Danvers, alongside Samuel L. Jackson, Ben Mendelsohn, Djimon Hounsou, Lee Pace, Lashana Lynch, Gemma Chan, Annett…

body:
Captain Marvel: Brie Larson, Jude Law e Ben Mendelsohn sulla copertina di Empire

Prima che la Carol Danvers di Brie Larson possa volare e sparare raggi dalle mani nei cinema di tutto il mondo in Captain Marvel in circa due mesi, deve prima vincere al gioco del marketing. E parte di questo comporta vedere la tua faccia su una rivista o due, come ci ha mostrato il nuovo numero di Empire Magazine.

title: Captain Marvel Details
body:
Captain Marvel is estimated to make 140-160 million dollars in its opening weekend. 

Details came out from the set visit and Captain Marvel will already have her powers when the movie starts and the Kree Skull war would be going on for centuries at this point but only have enough in the movie to move along the plot it doesn’t have tons of exposition. Half of the movie takes place in space while the other half is on Earth and it is non linear at points with influences from 90′s action movies and is set at the time it is to open up more space for the story to take place in.

Nick Fury has a big part in it and it brings some comedy with it but mostly serious. Her powers are in full effect here. Also Phillip Coulson in his first missions with Fury and haven’t experienced a lot of this before. 

http://collider.com/captain-marvel-plot-details/

https://boundingintocomics.com/2019/01/14/captain-marvel-projected-to-have-massive-opening-weekend-with-140-million-plus/
